IEEE Computer Society Madras Chapter is pleased to announce it's Mega ICT Quiz.
  
  Announcement & CFP: https://lnkd.in/gQG4t2SF
  
  Last date to register: 22nd Feb 2025
  
  About the Quiz: The IEEE Computer Society (CS) Madras Chapter is organizing a Mega ICT Quiz in a leadup to the 80th anniversary celebration of IEEE Computer Society which was founded in 1946. The Quiz will cover the Information and Communication Technology history, concepts, developments trends and current affairs.
  
  Who can participate: Students (College level and School level of 10th grade and above), Researchers, Faculty and Professionals can participate in the Quiz individually. 
  
  Quiz Pattern: The Quiz will be conducted in four stages. Online Prelims, Zonal Orals (in over 10 centres), Semifinal Orals (in two centres), and Final Orals (at Chennai). All Orals will be in-person physical events at various zonal locations in the IEEE Madras Geography.
  
  Certificate of Participation will be presented to all the participants of the online Prelims.
  
  Prizes
  
  Attractive Cash Prizes to all at Zonal, Semifinal & Final Orals.
  
  For toppers & 1st runner-ups (selectively), free ICT related books & subscription to periodicals will be presented. (Currently 12 gifts are available & more likely)
  
  Certificate of Appreciation to all the oral rounds participants. 
  
  The student finalists will additionally get free one year membership in IEEE & IEEE CS. 
  
  Registration Fee: Rs. 50 (fifty only)
  
  Register at https://bit.ly/ieeecs-ict-quiz-registration
  
  Tentative Dates
  
  Last date to Register: 22nd Feb 2025
  Online Prelims: by end of Feb 2025
  Zonal Orals: before end of Mar 2025 
  Semifinal Orals & Final Orals: mid Apr 2025

Greetings from SSN Coding Club,
  
  We?셱e excited to announce From Pixels to Vision Models, an engaging session on image processing and computer vision, hosted by us! With ImageCLEF 2025 now open, this is the perfect time to dive into cutting-edge techniques in computer vision and explore how models interpret images.
  
  Date: 21/02/25 (Friday)
  Time: 1PM - 3PM
  Place: CSE Seminar Hall
  
  What?셲 in Store? 
  1. Image Pre-processing (with a live demo) 
  2. Understanding Convolutional Neural Networks (CNNs) 
  3. YOLO (You Only Look Once) with a hands-on demo 
  4. Vision Transformers: The Future of Image Recognition 
  5. BLIP (Bootstrapped Language-Image Pre-training) and its applications 
  
  ?렞 Image Captioning Contest !
  Put your learning to the test with our week-long Image Captioning Challenge! Participants will build their own BLIP models using any dataset of their choice. Your models will be evaluated using a benchmark model developed by our team, ensuring a fair comparison.
  
  Looking forward to seeing you at the session and the contest!
  
  Best regards,
  
  (Note: This event is scheduled for 16th February 2025 at 2:00 PM.)

We are pleased to invite you to Radioverse: Hardware Project Expo, an excellent opportunity to showcase your technical expertise and innovation. This event is designed to provide a platform for students to present their groundbreaking hardware projects. It serves as a unique opportunity to gain industry-relevant experience and receive valuable feedback. This is a valuable opportunity to gain recognition, receive constructive feedback, engage with like-minded peers, and compete for prestigious recognition.
  
  Event Details:
  
  Date & Time: March 5, 2025 | 11:00 AM
  Venue: ECE Department
  Prize Pool: ??,000+ (First, Second, Third & Consolation Prizes)
  Registration Deadline: March 2, 2025
  Registration Fee: None
  Event Format:
  
  Round 1 ??Shortlisting: Projects will be evaluated based on innovation, feasibility, and technical execution. Selected teams will proceed to the final round.
  Round 2 ??Project Expo: Finalists will present their projects to a panel of judges and an audience for evaluation.
  Participation Guidelines:
  
  Open to student teams (1-3 members) with original, functional hardware projects.
  Each team will be provided a booth/table and must bring their own equipment. Presentations are encouraged.
  Judging criteria: 50% panel evaluation + 50% students feedback, based on innovation, technical quality, presentation, feasibility, and engagement.
  Voting: Conducted via QR codes or physical ballots, with one vote per person for one team.
  We encourage all aspiring innovators to participate and make the most of this platform.
  
  Registration Form:
  
  Interested participants can register using the following link:
  https://forms.gle/jW3954uJ4CTviYqW8
  
  
  (Note: This event is scheduled for 16th February 2025 at 11:00 AM.)

Greetings from IEEE PELS SSN!
 We are delighted to announce a new series, Techno Talks! We will be inviting distinguished guests, from alumni to industry experts, to talk to us about the exciting updates and emerging trends in the field of electronics and much more.
 
 To start us off, we are delighted to have Mr. Prashanth Pridhivi, a distinguished software R&D engineer and an alumnus of our EEE department, join us for a session on SoC/ASIC design verification of FPGAs on the 5th of February, 2025. Attendees will gain valuable insights into the fundamentals of FPGA-based design, verification techniques, challenges one might come across during verification, and the tools used in such hardware design validation.
 Do not worry if you're unsure whether to cut classes or stay back after college hours, as we're hosting this talk online via MS Teams! Do not miss this opportunity to enhance your knowledge and interact with an experienced professional in the field of FPGA design. Stay tuned for more updates!

 Date : 05/02/2025 ( Wednesday )
 Time : 8:00 pm 
 Mode : Online ( MS Teams )
 Link for the meeting will be shared at 6:00 pm, 5th February, with the attendees who fill the Google form above.

 SSN IEEE PELS

Subject: Invitation to the SSN Literary Fest 2024 - A Celebration of Words and Creativity
  
  Dear Book Enthusiasts,
  
  We are thrilled to invite you to the SSN Literary Fest 2024, a grand event dedicated to celebrating the art of storytelling, poetry, and intellectual discourse. Join us on April 5, 2024, at the,SSN Auditorium, Chennai, for a day filled with literary panels, author meet-and-greets, and exciting competitions.
  
 What to Expect?
  - Meet award-winning authors like Arundhati Roy and Amish Tripathi.
  - Participate in the 'Impromptu Debate Challenge' and 'Flash Fiction Contest'.

  Spots are limited! Register at ssnlitfest.com before March 25, 2024.
  
  Warm regards, 
  Ms. Anita Sharma 
  Coordinator, SSN Literary Fest

Subject: Reminder - Final Year Engineering Project Expo 2025
  
  Dear Final Year Students,
  
  This is a gentle reminder that the Final Year Engineering Project Expo 2025 will be held on May 15, 2025, at the SSN Engineering Block 2, Main Hall. This expo is a platform for you to showcase your hard work and innovations in fields such as robotics, AI, sustainable energy, and biomedical technology.
  
  All participating students are required to submit their project abstracts by April 20, 2025 via the SSN portal. Industry professionals from Tesla, TCS, and Siemens will be reviewing your projects, providing an excellent opportunity for recruitment and further research collaboration.
  
  We look forward to your participation.
  
  Best regards, 
  Dr. Sandeep Iyer 
  HOD, Department of Engineering Innovations

Subject: Invitation to SSN Artificial Intelligence Research Symposium 2025
  
  Dear Researchers and AI Enthusiasts,
  
  We are excited to invite you to the prestigious SSN Artificial Intelligence Research Symposium 2025, an event designed to bring together some of the brightest minds in AI and data science. This symposium will be held on July 18, 2025, at the SSN Research Hub, AI Laboratory.
  
  Why Attend?
  - Keynote Address by Dr. Lisa Tan, Head of AI at NVIDIA.
  - Workshops on AI in Healthcare, Finance, and Autonomous Systems.
  - Presentation of top AI research papers submitted by SSN students and faculty.
  - Career guidance from AI specialists working in Fortune 500 companies.
  
  Don't miss this incredible opportunity! Register before July 5, 2025, at ssnaihub.com.
  
  Best, 
  Dr. Karthik Srinivasan 
  Director, AI Research Center, SSN
